// DiscoveryService — read-only introspection surface for the Gibson daemon.
//
// This service answers "what can the authenticated caller currently use?" and
// is the backing for:
//
//   * opensource/adk/cmd/gibson-mcp (MCP tools driven by Claude Code)
//   * the dashboard's existing permissions-bridge migration
//     (app/api/components/permissions/route.ts, which currently fail-opens
//     to enabled=true for every visible catalog item; replaced by these RPCs
//     once the SDK v0.74.0 bump lands)
//   * any future Gibson CLI / third-party client
//
// Every RPC here is read-only. Mutations (toggle denies, install agents,
// register components, create missions) remain on DaemonService and
// DaemonAdminService; this file never writes.
//
// Tenant isolation is enforced by the standard FgaAuthzInterceptor — every
// RPC below registers a check of `member` against `tenant:<caller-tenant>`
// in fga_rpc_registry.go. Tenant_published items from other tenants are
// invisible by construction of the FGA model (model.fga v2 component type),
// not by filter logic in these handlers.
//
